\<h3 id=3D"PRD_SwapFee=E4=B8=8EImpactFee=E6=8B=86=E5=88=86=E5=B1=95=E7=A4=BA=

\<h4 id=3D"PRD_SwapFee=E4=B8=8EImpactFee=E6=8B=86=E5=88=86=E5=B1=95=E7=A4=BA=

\_P1-SwapFee"\>Swap Fee\</h4\>

\<p\>Swaps between assets inside the Hertzflow LP (HzLP) pool incur a \<strong=

\>dynamic swap fee\</strong\> to protect liquidity providers (LPs) and to keep=

the pool weights aligned with their targets. Swaps apply two layers of fee=

s:\</p\>

\<ul\>

\<li\>

\<p\>\<strong\>Base Fee Rate (base_bps)\</strong\> =E2=80=93 a flat fee applied t=

o every swap.\</p\>

\<ul\>

\<li\>

\<p\>Non-stables: \<code\>swap_fee_bps =3D 30\</code\> (0.30%)\</p\>\</li\>

\<li\>

\<p\>Stables: \<code\>stable_swap_fee_bps =3D 4\</code\> (0.04%)\</p\>\</li\>

\</ul\>\</li\>

\<li\>

\<p\>\<strong\>Dynamic Impact Fee Rate (Rebate or Tax, tax_bps)\</strong\> =E2=80=

=93 adjusts depending on whether your swap moves the pool \<strong\>toward\</s=

trong\> or \<strong\>away from\</strong\> the target weights.&nbsp;\</p\>

\<ul\>

\<li\>

\<p\>Non-stables: \<code\>tax_bps =3D 150\</code\> (1.5%)\</p\>\</li\>

\<li\>

\<p\>Stables: \<code\>stable_swap_fee_bps =3D 20\</code\> (0.2%)\</p\>\</li\>

\</ul\>\</li\>

\</ul\>

\<p\>\</p\>

\<p\>The \<strong\>dynamic impact fee rate\</strong\> is calculated as follows. T=

he protocol measures the difference between the \<strong\>current weightage\</=

strong\> and the \<strong\>target weightage\</strong\>:\</p\>

\<ul\>

\<li\>

\<p\>\<strong\>Initial Deviation (\</strong\>\<code\>init_diff =3D =EF=BD=9Cc% - t%=

=EF=BD=9C\</code\>\<strong\>)\</strong\>\<br\>

For instance, BTC target weight is 20%. If the pool currently holds only 1=

5%, then \<code\>init_diff =3D 5%\</code\>.\</p\>\</li\>

\<li\>

\<p\>\<strong\>Next Deviation (\</strong\>\<code\>next_diff =3D=EF=BD=9Cc%=E2=80=98=

\- t%=E2=80=98=EF=BD=9C\</code\>\<strong\>)\</strong\>\<br\>

After your swap, the deviation is recalculated. For instance, if your swap =

pushes BTC weight to 28%, then \<code\>next_diff =3D 8%\</code\>.\</p\>\</li\>

\</ul\>

\<p\>\</p\>

\<p\>Then the \<strong\>dynamic impact fee\</strong\> adjusts to reward behaviors=

that rebalances pool and :\</p\>

\<ul\>

\<li\>

\<p\>\<strong\>If next_diff &lt; init_diff =E2=86=92 Rebate\</strong\>\<br\>

Your swap brings the pool closer to balance. In this case, part of the fee=

is refunded. The rebate is capped so that the final fee never becomes nega=

tive.\</p\>\</li\>

\</ul\>

\<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;"\>

\<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl"\>

\<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=

: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence"\>FORMULA=

:

rebate_bps =3D tax_bps \* init_diff / t%

final_fee_bps =3D max(0, base_bps - rebate_bps)\</pre\>

\</div\>

\</div\>

\<p\>\</p\>

\<ul\>

\<li\>

\<p\>\<strong\>If next_diff =E2=89=A5 init_diff =E2=86=92 Tax\</strong\>\<br\>

Your swap makes the pool less balanced, so an extra tax is charged. If you=

help rebalance the pool, you get cheaper fees (rebate). If you push the po=

ol further out of balance, you pay more (tax).\</p\>\</li\>

\</ul\>

\<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;"\>

\<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl"\>

\<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=

: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence"\>FORMULA=

:

avg_diff =3D (init_diff + next_diff) / 2

capped_diff =3D min(avg_diff, t%)

tax_bps_adj =3D tax_bps \* capped_diff / t%

final_fee_bps =3D base_bps + tax_bps

The maximum loss is capped at (FEE_BPS_POWER - final_bps) / FEE_BPS_POWER.\<=

/pre\>

\</div\>

\</div\>

\<p\>\</p\>

\<div class=3D"panel" style=3D"background-color: \#EAE6FF;border-color: \#998D=

D9;border-width: 1px;"\>

\<div class=3D"panelContent" style=3D"background-color: \#EAE6FF;"\>

\<p\>\<strong\>EXAMPLE=EF=BC=9A\</strong\>\</p\>

\<ul\>

\<li\>

\<p\>BTC target =3D 20%.\</p\>\</li\>

\<li\>

\<p\>Pool initially has 0% BTC =E2=86=92 \<code\>init_diff =3D 20%\</code\>.\</p\>\<=

/li\>

\<li\>

\<p\>After swap, pool goes to 80% BTC =E2=86=92 \<code\>\<span class=3D"inline-c=

omment-marker" data-ref=3D"4bf543e4-f3b8-4704-991a-99bb0cf126b2"\>next_diff =

=3D 60%\</span\>\</code\>.\</p\>\</li\>

\<li\>

\<p\>Average deviation =3D 40%.\</p\>\</li\>

\</ul\>

\<p\>\<code\>final_bps =3D base_bps + 1.5% \* (20% / 20%) =3D 1.8%\</code\>\</p\>

\<p\>So the fee is \<strong\>much higher\</strong\> than the base fee =E2=80=94 a=

strong penalty for unbalancing the pool.\</p\>

\</div\>

\</div\>

\<p\>\</p\>

)\</p\>\</li\>

\<p\>\<strong\>Deviation Threshold (=CE=B4%):\</strong\> Each asset has a configu=

\<h4 id=3D"PRD_SwapFee=E4=B8=8EImpactFee=E6=8B=86=E5=88=86=E5=B1=95=E7=A4=BA=

\_P1-SwapFee.1"\>Swap Fee\</h4\>

\<p\>When you swap tokens inside the Hertzflow LP (HzLP) pool, you pay a \<str=

ong\>dynamic swap fee\</strong\>.\<br\>

This fee protects liquidity providers (LPs) and keeps the pool healthy and =

balanced.\</p\>

\<p\>Every swap includes \<strong\>two layers of fee rates\</strong\>:\</p\>

\<p\>\<strong\>Base Fee Rate\</strong\>\</p\>

\<p\>A small flat fee applied to every trade:\</p\>

\<ul\>

\<li\>

\<p\>\<strong\>Non-stable pairs\</strong\> (e.g. BTC/ETH, SUI/USDC): \<strong\>0.30=

%\</strong\>\</p\>\</li\>

\<li\>

\<p\>\<strong\>Stable pairs\</strong\> (e.g. USDC/USDT): \<strong\>0.04%\</strong\>\</=

p\>\</li\>

\</ul\>

\<p\>\<strong\>Impact Fee Rate (Rebate or Tax)\</strong\>\</p\>

\<p\>This part changes depending on how your swap affects the balance of the =

pool:\</p\>

\<ul\>

\<li\>

\<p\>\<strong\>If your trade helps rebalance the pool =E2=86=92 Rebate\</strong\>=

\</p\>

\<ul\>

\<li\>

\<p\>You get part of the fee refunded.\</p\>\</li\>

\<li\>

\<p\>Example: if the pool doesn=E2=80=99t have enough BTC and your swap adds =

BTC, your fees will be cheaper.\</p\>\</li\>

\</ul\>\</li\>

\<li\>

\<p\>\<strong\>If your trade pushes the pool further out of balance =E2=86=92 T=

ax\</strong\>\</p\>

\<ul\>

\<li\>

\<p\>You pay extra.\</p\>\</li\>

\<li\>

\<p\>Example: if the pool already has too much BTC and your swap adds even mo=

re BTC, you=E2=80=99ll be charged more.\</p\>\</li\>

\</ul\>\</li\>

\</ul\>

\<p\>The adjustment is capped:\</p\>

\<ul\>

\<li\>

\<p\>\<strong\>Maximum rebate\</strong\>: capped to the value of base rate.\</p\>\</=

li\>

\<li\>

\<p\>\<strong\>Maximum tax\</strong\>: capped so you never lose more than the set=

limit.\</p\>\</li\>

\</ul\>

\<div class=3D"panel" style=3D"background-color: \#EAE6FF;border-color: \#998D=

D9;border-width: 1px;"\>

\<div class=3D"panelContent" style=3D"background-color: \#EAE6FF;"\>

\<p\>For Example:\</p\>

\<ul\>

\<li\>

\<p\>BTC target weight =3D 20%\</p\>\</li\>

\<li\>

\<p\>Current BTC in pool =3D 0% (very low, underweight)\</p\>\</li\>

\<li\>

\<p\>After your swap, BTC goes up to 80% (way overweight)\</p\>\</li\>

\</ul\>

\<p\>=E2=9E=A1=EF=B8=8F Since your trade makes the imbalance worse, you pay:\<=

/p\>

\<ul\>

\<li\>

\<p\>Base Fee =3D 0.30%\</p\>\</li\>

\<li\>

\<p\>Tax =3D +1.5%\</p\>\</li\>

\<li\>

\<p\>\<strong\>Total Fee =3D 1.8%\</strong\>\</p\>\</li\>

\</ul\>

\<p\>This is a \<strong\>penalty for unbalancing the pool\</strong\>.\</p\>

\</div\>

\</div\>

\_P1-LPFee.1"\>LP Fee\</h4\>

\<p\>When you \<strong\>add or remove liquidity\</strong\> (minting or burning Hz=

LP), the system uses the same \<strong\>weight-balance logic\</strong\> as swap=

s\. The fee depends on whether your action moves the pool closer to its \<str=

ong\>target weights\</strong\> or pushes it further away.\</p\>

\<p\>\<strong\>Deviation Threshold (=CE=B4%)\</strong\>\</p\>

\<p\>Each asset has a configured \<strong\>maximum allowed deviation\</strong\> f=

rom its target weight.\<br\>

If the pool weight is pushed too far outside this bound, deposits/withdrawa=

ls may be restricted.\</p\>
